U . S T - bond drops over a point on hawkish Greenspan . U . S . Treasury prices fell sharply on Wednesday when Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan ' s Humphrey - Hawkins Congressional testimony turned out to be more hawkish than had been expected , analysts said . The 6 - 1 / 2 percent benchmark 30 - year bond fell about 1 - 1 / 4 point when headlines on the testimony were released . At 1015 EST / 1515 GMT , the bond was down a full point to 98 - 19 / 32 , yielding 6 . 73 percent . 
